
SOLID Design Principles in Java Application Development

. Refers to five design principles in object oriented programming, designed to reduce code rot and improve the value, function, and
  maintainability of software
. Helps develop less coupled code
. Are class level, object oriented design concepts that in conjunction with an extensive test suite, help one avoid code rot

The following are the five principles

1. Single Responsibility Principle
2. Open-Closed Principle
3. Liskov Substitution Principle
4. Interface Segregation Principle
5. Dependency Inversion Principle

